text:
Tried the new East Village branch on 10 'may for dinner
Yangzhou Fried Rice - no wok hey, slightly soggy rice but comes with fresh prawn
Broccoli with Cauliflower gravy tasted abit sour towards the end
har geong gai - was okay.
Service was excellent.

Their noodle dishes are unbeatable.
Wok hey is good, fire is controlled well.
Taste is good, not thirsty after eating.
Not too salty, not too sweet, they managed to find a balance.
Special mention: Singapore bee hoon (known as sin chew bee hoon/ sin chou mi fen)

Food is cheap at very generous portions for their rice and noodle dishes. I don't think this can be found anywhere else today.

Service is good. Friendly and helpful staff.
(Writing this review after an entire month of trying their dishes to ensure consistency)
One of the best zhi char stall in Punggol, portion sizes are good and prices are very reasonable. Definitely my family's go-to zhi char in Punggol 👍👍 Service is also very friendly and generous

Really really good food - almost like Malaysia ! :-)
Very tasty, price is reasonable, and staff is friendly.
We came back two days in a row :-)
Very reasonable priced and freshly prepared 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
